      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is a quick checklist for residential scaffolding safety before the crew goes up:\n\n1. **Base and Foundations**  \n   - Verify that the base plates are level and fully seated on the ground or concrete.  \n   - Check that all base plates are secured with anti‑vibration pins or stakes if required.  \n   - Inspect the base for any cracks, rust, or wear that could compromise stability.\n\n2. **Guardrails and Toeboards**  \n   - Confirm guardrails are installed at the correct height (typically 38–45 inches) and are securely fastened to the frame.  \n   - Ensure toeboards are in place at the bottom of each guardrail to prevent debris from falling.\n\n3. **Cross‑Bracing**  \n   - Look for proper cross‑bracing on all vertical and horizontal members to prevent lateral movement.  \n   - Check that all braces are tight, undamaged, and properly spaced according to the design plan.\n\n4. **Load‑Bearing Members**  \n   - Inspect the main uprights, ledgers, and transoms for any signs of bending, cracking, or corrosion.  \n   - Verify that all joints are properly tightened with",
